Parliament, Monday, 16 September 2019 – The Chairperson of the Select Committee on Land Reform, Environment, Mineral Resources and Energy, Ms Tebogo Modise, said she is shocked to hear of the tragic death of the Deputy Minister for Mineral Resources and Energy, Ms Bavelile Hlongwa, who tragically died last Friday in a car accident. Ms Modise said her thoughts and prayers are with Hlongwa family. “I know that there are no words that can truly erase the pain and loss. On behalf of the committee, I wish to extend our heartfelt sympathy and condolences to the Hlongwa family.” ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE SELECT COMMITTEE LAND REFORM, ENVIRONMENT, MINERAL RESOURCES AND ENERGY, MS TEBOGO MODISE. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Yoliswa Landu
